title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Identify all parts supplied by suppliers located in Germany whose individual stock value exceeds 0.0001 of the total stock value of all German suppliers. The stock value of each part is defined as ps_supplycost * ps_availqty. Use only suppliers from the nation ‘GERMANY’, compute the total stock value for Germany, and return only those parts whose value is greater than 0.0001 of that total. Output in Textfile.
